title: For Sale:  PIETTA M1861 COLT NAVY REPLICA
postcontent: This is a brand new, never used Pietta made replica of the Colt Model 1861 Navy revolver. The M1861 is a .36, and is based on the larger .44 caliber Army revolver, but slimmer and lighter. It is regarded as one of the most attractive of the Colt percussion handguns, and was made in far fewer numbers than the M1860 Army. Only 38,000 of these originals were made between 1861 and 1873.This beautiful replica is brand new. It has never been loaded or fired, and comes in the original box with all the original paperwork. It's steel framed, not brass. The cylinder is engraved with a naval battle scene, as were the originals, reflecting its use by the Union Navy, which preferred the lighter .36 to the heavy Army gun. It superceded the earlier issue .36, the Model 1851.This gun is ideal for Civil War re-enactments: it was used by both sides, and Confederate copies of it are known. It was used in the post-war settlement of the western frontier, and this revolver will be a great gun for the Cowboy Action shooter.Because it's percussion fired it is completely exempt from the never-sufficiently-to-be-cursed Gun Control Act of 1968 and all its provisions. Unless you live in some benighted hell-hole like the People's republic of new Jersey, you need not use and FFL to effect the transfer: it can be sent directly to your door.  I will ship via FEDEX at actual cost.After the expiration of the Rollin White Patent in 1872, conversion cylinders to allow the use of fixed ammunition went on the market: several present day companies make conversion cylinders for this gun: they're drop-in replacements requiring no gunsmithing and allow use of the .38 Long Colt cartridge.

New for 2016- the Griffin Armament Alpha takes the Recce 7's market leading attributes and patented baffle system and adds new-to-market features. The Alpha uses 6AL4V Titanium components to drop weight to 14.5 ounces for a .300 win mag rated suppressor that weighs less than most market 5.56mm offerings.
